{"key":"processedPost-7490645","value":{"id":7490645,"first":7490387,"last":22466563,"when":1191678101,"utime":"10/06/07 04:41 PM","content":"If they're for printing, let the caps begin to drop spores prior to picking. Don't let the caps flatten all the way out because that wastes your spores and makes a mess all over your grow chamber. If they're for eating, pick just prior to veil tear for best overall quality.<br /><br />I agree that paper is a poor printing medium.  Its porous surface attracts and holds contaminants, and the lime and acids used in production gives paper a wildly varied pH, which doesn't do much for the spores longevity.  I use foil.<br />RR","title":"Re: a few questions, LC and Print Making Vs Potency.","forum":"Mushroom Cultivation"}}